---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<Layout
  title={`AI-assisted Content Disclosure | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Disclosure of how Compute Current uses AI-assisted workflows for source extraction, classification, summarization, drafting, and editorial quality checks."
  canonicalPath="/ai-disclosure/"
>
  <main class="policy-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Intelligence board</a>
    <article class="policy-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">AI-assisted Disclosure</p>
      <h1>AI assists the workflow. Source facts set the boundary.</h1>
      <p class="policy-lede">
        Compute Current uses AI-assisted systems to help process source reporting into infrastructure intelligence. We use those systems as editorial tooling, not as a replacement for source attribution or quality controls.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>Where AI May Be Used</h2>
        <p>
          AI may assist with article extraction, source QA, infrastructure relevance scoring, taxonomy assignment, expert insight extraction, summarization, headline options, draft generation, repetition checks, and SEO checks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Where AI Is Constrained</h2>
        <p>
          Generated analysis must use source-specific facts and extracted expert insight fields. If extraction quality fails or the article lacks concrete infrastructure relevance, the system should avoid producing a long-form memo.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How Readers Can Verify</h2>
        <p>
          Article pages display source attribution and link to the original report. Structured data marks the original source as the basis for the generated memo while preserving Compute Current as the canonical URL for its own analysis page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="policy-link-row" aria-label="Transparency pages">
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>
        <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>
      </nav>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
